{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"930f54d9-d157-4c81-89ab-24f55c936871","content":"The issue is the **F# file compilation order** in the `.fsproj`. F# requires files to be listed in dependency order — `Services.fs` depends on `Domain.fs`, but `Services.fs` is listed first.\n\nFixing by reordering so `Domain.fs` comes before `Services.fs`:","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"toolu_vrtx_01CyVZbRPAaLB1Q29AtH8n4f","name":"report_intent","arguments":{"intent":"Fixing F# file order"},"type":"function"},{"toolCallId":"toolu_vrtx_01LmiJLvGizC1NodoH7asoR8","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/tmp/sv-5197d38448e3407a95d9d9b3cd7bb782/fsharp/BrokenOrder/BrokenOrder.fsproj","old_str":"    <Compile Include=\"Services.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Domain.fs\" />","new_str":"    <Compile Include=\"Domain.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Services.fs\" />"},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"edit the file at /tmp/sv-5197d38448e3407a95d9d9b3cd7bb782/fsharp/BrokenOrder/BrokenOrder.fsproj."}],"interactionId":"9a9a6ea6-d444-4f55-bda5-79f148c190cf","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The issue is clear. In F#, file compilation order matters - files can only reference types/modules defined in files that appear **before** them in the compilation order.\n\nIn the `.fsproj`, the order is:\n1. Services.fs\n2. Domain.fs\n3. Program.fs\n\nBut `Services.fs` depends on `Domain.fs` (it opens `BrokenOrder.Domain`), so `Domain.fs` must come before `Services.fs`. The correct order should be:\n1. Domain.fs\n2. Services.fs\n3. Program.fs","outputTokens":430,"requestId":"7C23:1290CA:AFB3BE:C80E8F:6A027933"},"id":"50b0aafa-6d01-485d-8631-779217477291","timestamp":"2026-05-12T00:50:03.940Z","parentId":"53708946-1844-4865-944e-57e28839366a"}
